19/07/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO's Deputy Supreme Allied Commander Europe, General John Reith, praised Macedonia's progress on the road to membership in the Alliance, during a meeting in Skopje with Defence Minister Lazar Elenovski and army chief Major General Miroslav Stojanovski on Wednesday (July 18th). Macedonia hopes to receive an invitation to NATO membership next year, during the Alliance's summit in Bucharest. (Vecer - 19/07/07; MIA - 18/07/07)
